LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1073
Introduced by Bosn, 25.
Read first time January 15, 2026
Committee: Transportation and Telecommunications
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Motor Vehicle Operator's License Act;
2 to amend section 60-462, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
3 2024; to define a term; to require commercial motor vehicle driver
4 training to include antitrafficking training as prescribed; to
5 provide powers and duties for the Attorney General; and to repeal
6 the original section.
7 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1073 LB1073
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 60-462, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 60-462 Sections 60-462 to 60-4,189 and section 2 of this act shall
4 be known and may be cited as the Motor Vehicle Operator's License Act.
5 Sec. 2. (1) For purposes of this section, commercial motor vehicle
6 driver training means any training course or educational program that is
7 offered in this state for the purpose of teaching or training any person
8 how to operate a commercial motor vehicle.
9 (2) The curriculum for any commercial motor vehicle driver training
10 that begins on or after January 1, 2027, shall include a minimum of
11 thirty minutes of antitrafficking training as prescribed by the Attorney
12 General.
13 (3)(a) No later than December 1, 2026, the Attorney General shall
14 prescribe the curriculum and training materials for the antitrafficking
15 training that is required under subsection (2) of this section.
16 (b) The Attorney General shall review and update such curriculum and
17 training materials at least once every three years to account for changes
18 and trends in human trafficking.
19 (4) The Attorney General may collaborate with any organization that
20 specializes in and offers training materials about the recognition,
21 prevention, and reporting of human trafficking for commercial motor
22 vehicle drivers.
23 (5) The Attorney General may adopt and promulgate rules and
24 regulations to carry out this section.
25 Sec. 3. Original section 60-462, Revised Statutes Cumulative
26 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
